						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Nicole wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Related to that, though this is a bit niche in comparison: the FDS BIOS has several functions that take pointer arguments inline after the <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">jsr</tt>. Though you have the labels already, it'd be nice if it could actually show up as <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">jsr LoadFiles / .dw $1234, $5678</tt> and so on automatically.<br /></div>There are a bunch of places throughout NES-land that do function parameters that way. <a href="http://bisqwit.iki.fi/source/nescom.html" class="postlink">nescom</a>'s clever-disasm calls it a TrailerParamRoutine.</div>

